					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The SNES controller just has two NES shift registers in series.  It works identically to the NES controller except there are 16 buttons vice 8.  Whatever you're doing to read NES buttons is the same routine you just keep reading the buttons until you have all 16 compared to just stopping at 8.  Nothing with the strobes or anything changes, the controller latches all 16 buttons on the single strobe similar to how the NES latches all 8.
<br />
<br />Kasumi has the order correct.</div>

